rComments: A good professor, knows his stuff, pretty friendly. Class seemed a bit too easy and basic  for a 2nd year French university class, but then other students still had problems even with that, so I suppose the professor adjusts to the level of his students. Textbook was very cheap for FRE240 so appreciated that

One of my favourite profs at UTM! :) He's super sweet and very approachable. Like every other class, attending his lectures is important but he makes time go back a lot quicker. Overall, I really enjoyed taking both of these courses with him and hopefully I can take more with him in the future! :)

He's a good prof. Interesting, though he teaches by just standing in front of the class & talking. Doesn't use aids. Tests were easy but he's a hard marker when it comes to assignments or essays. He likes to know his students & encourages them to see him at his office. I enjoyed going to lectures (sometimes) & he involved the class in activities.

Horrible lectures. Simply stands in the front of the class, rambles, and goes off on useless tangents. I had to learn everything from the textbook, he was no help. His syllabus is half a page and he doesn't explain his assignments. Most useless class of my life, I think I could learn more from staring at a wall.
Awesome prof! Makes class fun and easy to pay attention.  Material is easy and understandable.  Overall loved his class and him as a prof!
He's the best and most fun prof out there
NOT A CLASS FOR LAZY PEOPLE, PROCASTINATORS PEOPLE THAT HAVE ARROGANCE, TOO MUCH PRIDE, QUESTION PROFFS BELIEFS, OR PEOPLE THAT DO NOT AGREE WITH HIS PHILOSOPHERS THEORIES

A really easy course - starts off slow, then picks up the pace - but the workload is light and his tests are easy - easy to get an A in his class - just smile a lot and read the texts - he gives study guides to help - they do! Recommended
